Section 16: Removing Spring Boot
    Lecture 82: Create new H2 Console Configuration

1. Checking the H2ConsoleAutoConfiguration in Spring boot
 1.1 Open External Libraries in IntelliJ
    - Open Maven: org.springframework.boot.:spring-boot-autoconfigure:1.3.7.RELEASE
    - Look at the org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.h2.H2ConsoleAutoConfiguration

2. Open src/main/resources/application.properties file
 2.1 add "spring.autoconfigure.exclude[2]=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.h2.H2ConsoleAutoConfiguration"
     property in the application.properties file

3. Setup the New H2 Console Config
 3.1 Create new H2ConsoleConfig.java
    - ej.springframework.config.H2ConsoleConfig.java
 3.2 Add spring context @Configuration annotation above the H2ConsoleConfig class
 3.3 Implements new h2Console():ServletRegistration method

4. Test
  3.1 Start Server
  3.2 Open localhost:8080 and H2-console browser
  3.3 login and check weather still working application and the h2 testdb database (i.e, PRODUCT Table)